  "prompt": "Where can I get my short story reviewed?",
  "response": "There are several platforms and avenues where you can get your short story reviewed:\n\n1. **Writing Workshops**: Look for local or online writing workshops. These can provide valuable feedback from fellow writers. Websites like Meetup.com often list writing groups in your area.\n\n2. **Online Writing Communities**: Platforms like Wattpad, Scribophile, and Writing.com allow you to share your work and receive feedback from other writers and readers.\n\n3. **Critique Partners**: Find a critique partner through forums or social media (like Twitter or Reddit). Websites such as Absolute Write and The Writer\u2019s Beat can help you connect with others.\n\n4. **Beta Readers**: Reach out to friends, family, or social media contacts who may be interested in reading your story and providing feedback.\n\n5. **Literary Magazines**: Submit your story to literary magazines and journals. Many offer feedback during the submission process, though it may take time to receive a response.\n\n6. **Writing Blogs and Forums**: Websites like NaNoWriMo, Absolute Write Water Cooler, and other writing-focused forums can provide spaces where you can share your work for critique.\n\n7. **Workshops or Classes**: Enroll in a creative writing class, either online or at a local community college, where you can receive structured feedback.\n\n8. **Writing Contests**: Some contests offer feedback as part of their entry process, so you can consider participating in those as well.\n\nChoose the option that aligns best with your needs and the type of feedback you are looking for!",
